Phase 1 — Core broths, simple soups, and quick wins
Focus: stock-making, seasoning, sautéing aromatics, simple simmering, finishing with herbs and acid. 
learn basic chicken and vegetable stocks; master salt-to-acid balance; sauté mirepoix and deglaze.
- 1 Chicken Noodle Soup
- 2 Vegetable Soup 
- 3 Tomato Basil Soup (from canned tomatoes)
- 4 Miso Soup
- 5 Pho - Vegetarian

Phase 2 — Clear broths, noodle soups, gentle proteins
Focus: clearer stocks, balancing spice aromatics (for pho), handling delicate proteins (poached chicken, rare beef), and noodle timing.
make a simple beef bone stock and a clarified-ish light stock; practice resting/ thinly slicing proteins; time noodles precisely.
- 6 Vietnamese Pho Ga (chicken pho)
- 7 Beef Pho (Pho Bo)
- 8 Japanese Ramen (shoyu, then simple tonkotsu overview)
- 9 Chinese Hot and Sour Soup

Phase 3 — Purees, veloutés, and chilled basics
Focus: roasting veg, pureeing smoothly, making a velouté/roux, chilling (vichyssoise), and texture control.
roast before puree for depth; strain veloutés for silkiness; use an immersion blender safely
- 10 Potato Leek Soup or Vichyssoise (chilled french version)
- 10.5 Creamy Chicken & Wild Rice Soup 
- 11 Butternut Squash Soup
- 12 Carrot and Ginger Purée
- 13 Cauliflower Velouté
- 14 Cream of Broccoli (broccoli‑cheddar style)

Phase 4 — Legumes, beans, and hearty vegetarian protein soups
Focus: soaking/pressure‑cooking legumes, building long-simmer flavor, seasoning pulses, and one‑pot techniques.
learn doneness of different pulses; use aromatics and acid to brighten; finish with herbs and oil
- 15 Classic Lentil Soup (red and brown variations)
- 16 Turkish Lentil Soup
- 17 Cannellini Bean Soup (Tuscan)
- 18 Chickpea and Spinach Soup
- 19 Black Bean Soup (Latin style)

Phase 5 — Chowders, bisques, seafood, and dairy finishes
Focus: dairy emulsions, gentle simmering of seafood, roux vs. slurry, straining for bisques, and balancing richness.
avoid overcooking shellfish; temper dairy; use shells for stock; clarify and reduce for bisque intensity.
- 20 Corn Chowder
- 21 Crab and Sweet Corn Chowder
- 22 New England Clam Chowder (creamy)
- 23 Lobster Bisque
- 24 French Bouillabaisse

Phase 6 — Hearty meat stews, international classics, and advanced techniques
Focus: long braises, gelatin extraction (oxtail), complex spice balancing, pickled/fermented flavor (kimchi, borscht), and showpiece stocks/consommés
plan multi‑day stocks for deep flavor; learn browning, deglazing, and fat management; practice acid and heat control for regional soups.
- 25 Beef Stew
- 26 Oxtail Soup
- 27 Hungarian Goulash Soup
- 28 Chicken and Dumplings
- 29 Gumbo (seafood and chicken/sausage versions)
- 30 Chili
- 31 Mexican Pozole (hominy and pork)
- 32 Spanish Sopa de Ajo (garlic soup)
- 33 Thai Tom Yum Goong (hot‑sour shrimp soup)
- 34 Korean Kimchi Jjigae
- 35 Borscht (beet soup with beef)
- 36 Italian Ribollita
- 37 Gazpacho
- 38 Salmorejo
- 39 Cucumber Dill Cold Soup
- 40 Chicken Tortilla Soup
- 41 Oxtail Soup (if you’d like to repeat as a showpiece technique)